This function generate the null distribution of T_eta, should be run before calculating TWT. Please see Setp 2 in our manuscript for more information.

generate_null_distribution_T3(m, n, cov_mat, cutoff_value)

Arguments

m

Dimension.

n

Number of the generated sample size.

cov_mat

Covariance matrix for generating random samples.

cutoff_value

Truncated value, should be in 0 to 1 and must contain 1.

Value

Null distribution matrix with number of rows equal n and number of columns equal length of cutoff value minus 1.
